But as far as I was concerned this was an industry that remorselessly piled on the profits. The previous few years had seen an epic expansion of bank returns. The largest 1,000 banks in the world reported aggregate pre-tax profits of almost $800 billion in fiscal year 2007-08, almost 150% higher than in 2000-01. Total returns to shareholders in big banks in America, Britain and the euro area rose by 150% between 2002 and 2007.
